# Variable Naming Conventions

## Rules

1. **camelCase** for all variables (e.g., `$itemDetails`, `$searchTerms`, `$requestDescription`)
2. **Descriptive names** - avoid single letters or abbreviations (e.g., `$query` not `$q`, `$item` not `$i`)
3. **Closure parameters** - use `$query` or `$subQuery` for query builder, `$item` or `$row` for collection items

## Examples

```php
// ❌ BAD
$q = DB::table('tabItem')->where(...);
$item_details = Item::find($id);
$search_str = explode(' ', $request->search);
->when($request->q, function ($q) use ($request) { return $q->where(...); });

// ✅ GOOD
$itemsQuery = DB::table('tabItem')->where(...);
$itemDetails = Item::find($id);
$searchTerms = explode(' ', $request->search);
->when($request->q, function ($query) use ($request) { return $query->where(...); });
```
